The National Publicity Secretary of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Mallam Bolaji Abdullahi, has joined the train of defections in the ruling party. Abdulahi on Wednesday, submitted his resignation letter to the party leadership in Abuja.
National Daily gathered that Abdullahi, in a statementÂ  in Abuja, on Wednesday, explained that his resolve to quit APC was prompted by series of unpleasant developments unfolding in the ruling party
He further said that more than once, his loyalty to the party has been questioned, adding that his views have also been opposed on different occasions.
He added that he has suffered insubordination from some of deputies.

The defection came after report that he is still in APC, while his political principal, Dr. Bukola Saraki, has dumped the party for the PDP.

Meanwhile, he is yet to indicate his next destination but all fingers point to the PDP.


